                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.0012Anti-War/281: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-18T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1928—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>283. Your No. 248, August 18, 4 p.m. Department thought that France would not
                    have any objection to Morocco’s adherence, but instead would welcome it. As it
                    appears that objection does exist, the Department does not at this time desire
                    to push matter further. You may so inform the Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
